{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nAfter dropping the bot + FFO, EVERY doc/reference to autosubmit, the auto-lander, the `land`/`land-status` command, `lander_down`, or the FFO Gerrit workflow is inaccurate. This is a comprehensive prose sweep, not just the top-level guides.\n\n## What — comprehensive grep-driven prose sweep\nSweep the repo's **prose docs** (top-level `*.md`, `docs/**/*.md`, inline `--help`/comment text) and correct/remove every reference to the old model. Search terms (case-insensitive): `autosubmit`, `auto-lander`/`autolander`, `land-contract`/`land_contract`, `land-status`, `lander_down`, `fast forward only`/`fast-forward-only`/`FFO`, `rebase-on-behalf`, `Autosubmit label`, `set Autosubmit`, `land <change> --wait`, \"both votes green ≠ lands\" trap language.\n\nFiles rewritten to the new model: CLAUDE.md (Git-workflow land section), CONTRIBUTING.md (§2e land flow, feature-branch §4c/§4e land pointers, troubleshooting), README.md (landing pointer), docs/your-first-change.md (walkthrough land step), docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md (drop the autolander SSM-token row).\n\nBanner-only (historical decision records, prose left intact): ADR 0040 + ADR 0042 get a \"Superseded by ADR 0047\" banner. Light pointer-note (submit type is now Rebase-If-Necessary; prior-model logic left for a separate review): ADR 0025, ADR 0041.\n\n## New model documented everywhere\nLand via a plain Gerrit **Submit** once **LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1** (and no unresolved comments); `main` is **Rebase-If-Necessary**, so Gerrit rebases onto the tip and submits server-side/atomically — no pre-rebase in the common case. On a **textual** conflict only: `git fetch && git rebase origin/main`, re-push, re-Submit. **No bot, no Autosubmit label, no land/land-status command, no lander_down fallback.** Post-merge `main` CI (test.yml on push) + manual revert is the bounded-risk safety net.\n\n## Scope notes (division with siblings)\n- **infra/** autolander references are sibling **bcf0**'s scope, NOT this story — this sweep is prose docs only.\n- The **`land`/`land-status` command was a standalone argparse `main` in infra/autolander/land.py (removed by d0e5), NOT a rebar CLI subcommand or MCP tool** — confirmed: no `src/rebar/cli` `land` subcommand and no CLI/MCP reference doc mentions it. So there is **no `--help`/drift-gated/MCP reference doc to regenerate** for it.\n- **CLAUDE.local.md** is git-ignored (`.gitignore`), so it is NOT a committed repo file and cannot be part of this change; its landing guidance already matches the new plain-Submit model (verified). No repo edit; refreshed locally out-of-band if ever needed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Old-model ABSENCE in prose: `git grep -icE \"autosubmit|auto-?lander|land-contract|land-status|lander_down|fast[- ]forward[- ]only|\\bFFO\\b|rebase[- ]on[- ]behalf|land <change>|--wait|both votes green\" -- '*.md'` returns hits ONLY in the two superseded ADRs (docs/adr/0040, docs/adr/0042 — historical prose under a supersession banner), docs/adr/0047 itself, the light pointer-notes on docs/adr/0025 + docs/adr/0041, and the ADR-0047 filename inside hyperlinks. (GitHub-mirror \"fast-forward only\" in docs/adr/0010 + docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md is a different concept and out of scope.)\n- [ ] New-model PRESENCE: the rewritten landing sections in CLAUDE.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, README.md, and docs/your-first-change.md each contain the phrase `Rebase-If-Necessary` — verify with `for f in CLAUDE.md CONTRIBUTING.md README.md docs/your-first-change.md; do grep -q \"Rebase-If-Necessary\" \"$f\" || echo \"MISSING: $f\"; done` printing nothing.\n- [ ] Supersession banners present: `grep -l \"Superseded by \\[ADR 0047\\]\" docs/adr/0040-*.md docs/adr/0042-*.md` lists both files.\n- [ ] docs-index / dead-link checker stays green: `python scripts/check_docs_index.py --check` exits 0.\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783992427394984001,"uuid":"92ba4136-a595-4870-baad-fac51d4ffd89"}